  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do you deposit cash at an ATM?",
  "response": "Depositing cash at an ATM is generally a straightforward process. Here's how you can typically do it:\n\n1. **Locate an ATM:** Find an ATM that accepts cash deposits. Usually, these are ATMs that belong to the bank where you have your account, although some banks may allow deposits from other banks.\n\n2. **Insert Your Card:** Insert your debit card into the ATM card slot.\n\n3. **Enter Your PIN:** Enter your Personal Identification Number (PIN) to access your account.\n\n4. **Choose Transaction Type:** Select the option for deposits on the screen. You may have an option to deposit cash or checks.\n\n5. **Prepare Your Cash:** Organize your cash. Ensure the bills are flat, without creases or folded corners.\n\n6. **Insert Cash:** Follow the on-screen instructions to insert your cash into the deposit slot. In some ATMs, you may need to put the cash into an envelope first, but many newer machines accept cash directly without an envelope.\n\n7. **Confirm Amount:** The ATM should automatically count the cash and display the amount deposited on the screen. Verify the total is correct.\n\n8. **Complete Deposit:** Confirm that the amount is correct and follow any additional instructions. You might be asked if you want a receipt.\n\n9. **Finish Transaction:** Once you're finished, end the transaction and retrieve your card. You may also want to take the receipt if you opted for one.\n\n10. **Check your Account:** It\u2019s a good practice to check your account balance after the deposit to ensure it has been credited correctly.\n\nNote that the specific steps can vary slightly depending on the bank and the type of ATM you are using. If you encounter issues or if it's your first time, many ATMs have a help or assistance button, or you can ask for help from the bank staff.",
